The paper discusses the development and history of information metrics, which involves the use of bibliometrics, scientometrics, informetrics, and webometrics. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of citations for historical reconstruction, which could also place it in the sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.HIST (Computing and Society).
